Pago 113, 1. 22. Comes de Ew. Raoul de Brienne, comte d’Eu et de Guines, had been detained a prisoner in England since his capture at Caen in 1346. He did not regain his sreedom until near the end of October, 1350. At first received with favour by the French king John, he was suddenly arrested and executed. The day of his death is usually stated to be the 19th November, but there is reason sor adopting the 18th. — Luce's Froissart, iv. xlviii. The story of his intrigue with the queen, Bona os Luxemburg, is an idle tale. She had already died on the 11th September, 1349.
